member.example:
This sample shows how to encode a barcode using the Code39 type, saving it to a file.

             imgBarCoder.EncodeBarcode(ImgBarCoder.ImgBarCoder.BarcodeType.Code39, "12345678", 400, 200)
             imgBarCoder.SaveImage("C:\Barcode.bmp", ImgBarCoder.ImgBarCoder.OutputFormat.BMP)

             imgBarCoder.EncodeBarcode(ImgBarCoder.ImgBarCoder.BarcodeType.Code39, "12345678", 400, 200);
             imgBarCoder.SaveImage("C:\Barcode.bmp", ImgBarCoder.ImgBarCoder.OutputFormat.BMP);

This sample shows how to encode a barcode using the Code39 type, saving it to a file.

